context_meta.author: nanook
context_meta.title: 5 Financial Mistakes New Graduates Must Avoid
context_meta.summary: How graduates approach financial planning in the first few years after college can set the tone for their financial habits down the road. Unreasonable spending habits often take over as an escape from the daily grind, and entire paychecks are spent on regular expenses (such as rent and utilities), purchases (such as an automobile and furniture) and luxury items (such as travel and an oversized television). Although you should enjoy your newfound freedom, you should also strive to save a nice portion of your paychecks.
